<p>
<div class="row">
	<div class="span10">
		<h2><center>Eazesportz.com - What you can do with our<p>
			iPad Management Console!</center></h2>
		<p>
		<h4>Live updates during a game are what your fans are looking for. With our management console, you can have one or more people entering
			live stats. Maybe one for offense and one for defense:</h4>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<h5>Offensive Stats</h5>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<h5>Defensive Stats</h5>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<%= image_tag "FC_OffenseStatsPortrait.png" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<%= image_tag "FC_DefLiveStatsPortrait.png" %>
			</div>
		</div>
		<h4>One of your players scored. The stat and score is entered by your stats keeper and a score log is automatically generated.<h4>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<h5>Scoring Play Entered</h5>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<h5>Scoring Play Automatically Generated</h5>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<%= image_tag "FC_LiveScoreStat.png" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<%= image_tag "FC_OffLiveGameLog.png" %>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p>
		<h>Because you want to provide your fans with the ultimate experience, you also have two people on the field. One with a digital camera and the
			other with a video camera. Both have an iPad with our management console installed and the Apple iPad Camera Connection Kit. You can get the
			connection kit from an Apple store or other online stores. There are a number of instructional videos on YouTube on how to use the kit.</h4>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<h5>Camera Connection Kit:</h5>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<h5>Tag Photo for Scoring Play</h5>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<%= image_tag "AppleCameraConnectionKit.jpeg" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span4 offset1">
				<%= image_tag "FC_PhotoTagPlayPortrait.png" %>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p>
		<h5>If one or both of your live photographers catch the scoring play, they can tag that photo or video to the automatically generated play. 
			If there are more than one photo or video they can tag them all for that play.<h5>
		<h4>Your fans can then access the photo or video using our iPhone app:</h4>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span2">
				<h5>User Selects Play:</h5>
			</div>
			<div class="span2 offset1">
				<h5>Photo Tagged for Play:</h5>
			</div>
			<div class="span2 offset1">
				<h5>Video Tagged for Play:</h5>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span2">
				<%= image_tag "ios_GamePlayTagPhotoVideo.png" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span2 offset1">
				<%= image_tag "ios_GamePlayTagPhoto.png" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span2 offset1">
				<%= image_tag "ios_GamePlayTagVideo.png" %>
			</div>
		</div>
		<h4>This is just one example of what you can do with our iPad management console. You can also post photos or videos throughout the game that may be
			of interest and tag them by player or players if your choose to do so.</h4>
		<p>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span2">
				<%= link_to "Back to Info", info_path, class: "btn btn-medium btn-primary" %>
			</div>
		</div>
</div>

	</div>
</div>
